******
[1] Alabama (Mobile County)
Date: Fri 13 Jun 2014
Source: Hattiesburg American, Associated Press (AP) report [edited]
http://www.hattiesburgamerican.com/story/news/local/2014/06/13/whooping-cough-cases/10378765/


Health officials in Mobile say there's been an alarming recent rise in the number of whooping cough cases in the area. Whooping cough, the common name for pertussis, is highly contagious. Those infected experience uncontrollable violent coughing that can make it hard to breathe.

Local media reports say the Mobile County Health Department has recorded 18 cases, 10 of which have been confirmed, between 25 May 2014 and 11 Jun 2014. Multiple other possible cases were being investigated. There were just 8 confirmed and probable cases in the county in 2013.

