[3] Ohio (Logan County)
Date: Fri 6 Jun 2014
Source: Springfield (OH) News-Sun [edited]
http://www.limaohio.com/news/news/1407377/Bellefontaine-schools-see-pertussis-outbreak


The outbreak of pertussis, more commonly known as whooping cough, started in April 2014 with 2 confirmed cases involving Bellefontaine Elementary School students. During May 2014, the district's number of confirmed pertussis cases jumped to 10. "At first, they were in one part of Bellefontaine City Schools, and now it has spread to different grades," Hoddinott said.

The school system sent out a letter and texts to parents alerting them about the outbreak. Hoddinott said it is not unusual for Bellefontaine to see 10 confirmed cases in a year, but the concern came because they were all so closely related. "There are probably more cases that have not been diagnosed, but those (10 confirmed cases) are the ones who are sickest and have gone through a doctor and were tested," he said.

Phone calls to Champaign Health District officials for an update were not returned.

[Byline: Brian Bondus]

